<subSubSection id="C33AA39E3852FFFCFE14FCC82A85052A" box="[416,479,786,810]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9FF0153852FFFCFE14FCC82A85052A" blockId="21.[416,479,786,810]" box="[416,479,786,810]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<figureCitation id="131BEC903852FFFCFE14FCC82A85052A" box="[416,479,786,810]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[129,168,1812,1836]" captionTargetBox="[128,1451,1207,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[128,1451,1207,1796]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 5. a. Megaleporinus macrocephalus, NUP 1838, 470.0 mm SL, rio Chopim, Cruzeiro do Iguaçu, State of Paraná. b. Megaleporinus obtusidens, 190.8 mm SL, fresh specimen, uncat. c. Megaleporinus piavussu, 148.9 mm SL, fresh specimen, uncat. d. Schizodon altoparanae, MZUSP 41102, holotype, 282.2 mm SL, rio Paraná, in front of Jupiá, Três Lagoas, State of Mato Grosso do Sul. e. Schizodon borellii, 207.5 mm SL, fresh specimen, uncat. f. Schizodon nasutus, NUP 2495, 160.0 mm SL, Itaipu Reservoir, Santa Helena, State of Paraná." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678405/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFE14FCC82A85052A" bold="true" box="[416,479,786,810]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E3852FFFCFF12FC882F850748" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9FF0153852FFFCFF12FC882EFD0708" blockId="21.[129,768,850,1162]" lastBlockId="21.[813,1451,176,264]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Body elongated; greatest depth contained 2.8 to 3.5, caudal peduncle depth 7.9 to 9.1 times in SL; head length 3.5 to 4.7, predorsal distance 2.0 to 2.2, caudal peduncle length 
<quantity id="4CD85DF03852FFFCFF78FC682A0905CA" box="[204,339,946,970]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0574" metricValueMax="2.2098" metricValueMin="1.905" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="in" value="8.1" valueMax="8.7" valueMin="7.5">7.5 to 8.7 in</quantity>
SL; snout length 2.1 to 2.7, horizontal orbital diameter 3.7 to 5.1 and least interorbital width 1.9 to 2.4. Mouth subterminal; premaxilla and dentary with 3 teeth, no maxillary teeth. Lateral line with 41-44 pored scales; transverse series above lateral line with 6 or 7 scale rows and below with 5 or 6 scale rows. Dorsal fin with 11 or 12, pectoral fin with 15-19, pelvic fin with 9 and caudal fin with 19 rays (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE43852FFFCFC57FF6A2FE906C8" author="Britski" box="[995,1203,176,200]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Britski" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="441 - 75" refId="ref79344" refString="Britski HA, Birindelli JLO, Garavello JC. A new species of Leporinus Agassiz, 1829 from the upper rio Parana basin (Characiformes, Anostomidae) with redescription of L. elongatus Valenciennes, 1850 and L. obtusidens (Valenciennes, 1837). Pap Avulsos Zool. 2012; 52 (37): 441 - 75." type="journal article" year="2012">
Britski 
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB81FF6B2F3106C8" box="[1077,1131,176,200]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
, 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). Ground color silvery; three dark-brown rounded blotches over lateral line. Dorsal fin whitish; pectoral, pelvic, anal and caudal fins yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9FF0153852FFFCFC99FEEB2F850748" blockId="21.[813,1247,305,329]" box="[813,1247,305,329]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFC99FEEB2F3F0749" bold="true" box="[813,1125,305,329]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Maximum standard length.</emphasis>
410.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E3852FFFCFC99FEAB2F980789" box="[813,1218,369,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9FF0153852FFFCFC99FEAB2F980789" blockId="21.[813,1218,369,393]" box="[813,1218,369,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFC99FEAB28E50789" bold="true" box="[813,959,369,393]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
Upper rio 
<collectingRegion id="49E43EF73852FFFCFB87FEAB2F260789" box="[1075,1148,369,393]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Paraná</collectingRegion>
basin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E3852FFFCFC99FE682E26054A" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9FF0153852FFFCFC99FE682E26054A" blockId="21.[813,1452,434,842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFC99FE6828CC07CA" bold="true" box="[813,918,434,458]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFC1DFE682FF507CA" baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[937,1199,434,458]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFC1DFE682FF507CA" box="[937,1199,434,458]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFA22FE6928C007EA" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFA22FE6928C007EA" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE43852FFFCFC70FE082FE407EA" author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[964,1214,466,490]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. Ramirez 
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFA9DFE092E0507EA" box="[1321,1375,466,490]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2016) described the new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFB98FE282F9D040A" authorityName="Ramirez, Birindelli, Galetti Junior" authorityYear="2016" box="[1068,1223,498,522]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB98FE282F9D040A" box="[1068,1223,498,522]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and proposed the new combination. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE43852FFFCFC08FDC82FD5042A" author="Britski" box="[956,1167,530,554]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Britski" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="441 - 75" refId="ref79344" refString="Britski HA, Birindelli JLO, Garavello JC. A new species of Leporinus Agassiz, 1829 from the upper rio Parana basin (Characiformes, Anostomidae) with redescription of L. elongatus Valenciennes, 1850 and L. obtusidens (Valenciennes, 1837). Pap Avulsos Zool. 2012; 52 (37): 441 - 75." type="journal article" year="2012">
Britski 
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFBBFFDC92F18042A" box="[1035,1090,530,554]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
redescribed 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFAACFDC92EF1042A" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[1304,1451,530,554]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFAACFDC92EF1042A" box="[1304,1451,530,554]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described the new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFBDBFDE92FB1044A" baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1135,1259,563,586]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFBDBFDE92FB1044A" box="[1135,1259,563,586]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(under 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFA8FFDE92EF8044A" box="[1339,1442,563,586]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFA8FFDE92EF8044A" box="[1339,1442,563,586]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Leporinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from the upper rio 
<collectingRegion id="49E43EF73852FFFCFC47FD882F62046A" box="[1011,1080,594,618]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Paraná</collectingRegion>
basin. 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFB30FD882E25046A" baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1156,1407,594,618]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB30FD882E25046A" box="[1156,1407,594,618]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Megaleporinus piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by having 39 or 40, rarely 41, pored scales in the lateral line, and mouth terminal, except in some large adults with somewhat subterminal mouth (
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB5CFD692E5E04CA" box="[1256,1284,691,714]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">vs.</emphasis>
41 to 43, rarely 
<quantity id="4CD85DF03852FFFCFC99FD08283B04EA" box="[813,865,722,746]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1176" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="in" value="44.0">44 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFCDCFD0928A204EA" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[872,1016,722,746]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFCDCFD0928A204EA" box="[872,1016,722,746]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and mouth directed somewhat or entirely downward in 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFC0DFD292F12050A" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[953,1096,754,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Leporinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obtusidens">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFC0DFD292F12050A" box="[953,1096,754,778]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. obtusidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFB61FD292E74050A" baseAuthorityName="Britski, Birindelli, Garavello" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[1237,1326,755,778]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="piavussu">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB61FD292E74050A" box="[1237,1326,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">piavussu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the common name of 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B963852FFFCFBA3FCC92F8D052A" baseAuthorityName="Garavello, Britski" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1047,1239,786,810]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Anostomidae" genus="Megaleporinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrocephalus">
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFBA3FCC92F8D052A" box="[1047,1239,786,810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">M. macrocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“ 
<emphasis id="B9542C073852FFFCFB58FCC92EC0052A" box="[1260,1434,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">piavuçu, piaussu</emphasis>
”, but these are different species and should not be confused.
</paragraph>
